Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?feat:=20admin=20dashboard=20app=20=E2=80=94=20d?=
 =?UTF-8?q?ashboard,=20students,=20content,=20moderation,=20settings?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Full admin experience, wired to the real backend admin endpoints instead of
the mockup's hardcoded data. Adapted the web mockup's sidebar layout to a
mobile Drawer + top bar, since a persistent sidebar doesn't fit a phone
screen.

- AppShell now resolves the logged-in user's role after login (GET
  /users/me) and routes ADMIN accounts into AdminShell instead of the
  normal student bottom-nav experience. If the role check fails for any
  reason, falls back to the student view rather than blocking the app.
- Dashboard: real KPIs, daily-activity bar chart, filière-distribution
  donut, and a top-students list (sorted client-side from /admin/users,
  since there's no dedicated leaderboard-for-admin endpoint).
- Students: list with search/filiere/status filters, detail sheet with
  real stats (XP, streak, exercises solved/attempted), suspend/reactivate/
  ban, and promote-to-admin.
- Content: exercises + contests tabs. Exercise create/edit form (full
  fields incl. choices with a radio for the correct answer — matches the
  backend's atomic choice-replace). Contest edit covers metadata (title/
  year/filière); editing a contest's actual questions isn't built here,
  noted as a follow-up if needed. Delete with confirmation on both.
- Moderation: stats, filter by reported/published, validate or remove a
  reported post.
- Settings: general info, gamification XP/penalty rules, and the
  maintenance-mode toggle (applies immediately via PATCH, not tied to the
  Save button).

Deliberately NOT included, since there's no backend support for it:
- The mockup's "IA NEXA (API key)" settings card — PlatformSettings has no
  field for this at all; building the UI would be pure decoration.
- The mockup's "Analytique" screen (12-month trends, per-school engagement)
  — the backend only tracks the last 7 days, no historical/monthly
  aggregation exists. Building fake monthly charts felt worse than not
  having the screen.
- The mockup's live "Activité récente" feed — there's no audit-log/events
  table backing it; it's pure mock data in the original file.

Known pre-existing backend gap surfaced while wiring settings: the
"xpPerDirectAnswer" field is stored and editable but not actually applied
anywhere in exercises/contests grading (each exercise's own xpBase is
always used instead). Left as-is since fixing it is a backend change, not
in scope here — flagging for a future patch.
